<h1 class="text-primary">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    <strong>Effective Date:</strong> August 20, 2025
</p>

<p>
    ABC Retailers ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of our users and customers. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you interact with our website, applications, and services. By using our platform, you agree to the practices described herein.
</p>

<p>
    We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as your name, contact details, delivery address, and any other identifiers necessary to fulfill your orders and provide support. Additionally, we gather transactional data related to your purchases, including product selections, payment status, and delivery preferences. Our system may also log technical data such as your IP address, browser type, device information, and usage patterns to help us improve performance and security. If you upload files—such as images or documents—they are stored securely and used solely for the intended purpose.
</p>

<p>
    Your information is used to process orders, communicate with you, enhance our services, and ensure the security and integrity of our platform. We may also use your data to comply with legal obligations and to analyze usage trends that help us improve our offerings. We do not sell your personal data to third parties. However, we may share it with trusted service providers such as cloud hosting platforms (including Microsoft Azure), payment processors, and logistics partners who assist in delivering our services. In cases where disclosure is required by law or necessary to protect our rights, we may share information with legal authorities.
</p>

<p>
    All data is stored using industry-standard encryption and access controls. Our infrastructure is hosted on secure platforms that comply with international data protection standards. Depending on your location, your data may be transferred to and processed in countries with different privacy laws. We ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your information during such transfers.
</p>

<p>
    You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain processing activities. Where applicable, you may also withdraw consent or lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority. To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@abcretailers.com">privacy@abcretailers.com</a>.
</p>

<p>
    We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience and analyze usage. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings. Please note that disabling cookies may affect certain functionalities of our platform.
</p>

<p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will post any updates on this page and revise the effective date accordingly.
</p>

<p>
    If you have any questions or concerns about this policy or your personal data, please contact our Privacy Office at <a href="mailto:privacy@abcretailers.com">privacy@abcretailers.com</a> or visit us at 123 Commerce Lane, Johannesburg, South Africa.
</p>
